content.description: Really easy, really short. If you can do a pull up you can climb this.
content.protection: Boulder Pad but not really necessary
content.location: Start heading north on 95. Take exit 75 - auburn, and head north on route 4 to Philips. Turn right onto Rt. 142. turn right onto wheeler hill road. Trailhead 2 miles in on left. Park on right side follow path about 1/4 of a mile. Boulder on right.   Route is on the smallest of the three fragments.

content.description: There were two rusty pitons (one of which got pulled out when I was cleaning the gear), indicating that old school hardmen have probably climbed it before. I found the gear a bit tricky to place, and led it with pre-placed gear. I'm tentatively calling it Northeast Overhang 5.10+. If anyone is aware of a previous free ascent please let me know. youtube.com/watch?v=LpKwMK9â€¦
content.protection: small cams and medium sized nuts.
content.location: This is "Crack Project 19" in the mini guide. Starting at the center of Daggett Rock, ascend the arching crack, then traverse left around the arete (crux), traverse further left on crimps and pull the roof.
Climb left slanting arete to the top.

content.description: The boulder is 80'x'50' and 25' tall. The granite boulder is broken into three large pieces. The boulder sees many vistors/hikers each year but few venture here for the small number of tall boulder problems.
